
[1]anodyne

   AN'ODYNE, [Gr. pain.]

   Any medicine which allays pain, or causes sleep, as an opiate,
   paregoric, narcotic, &c.

        AN'ODYNE, a. Assuaging pain; causing sleep, or insensibility.
